comments.body: @christinach It doesn't look suppressed to me. https://github.com/pulibrary/marc_liberation/issues/824 indicates that a suppressed record should have a '950$a' value of "Suppress from publishing Bibliographic Enrichment" This has a call number value in that subfield.

@hackartisan I mentioned in our meeting about a discrepancy in #824 regarding the suppressed. I see in https://princeton.alma.exlibrisgroup.com/ng/page;u=%2Frep%2Faction%2FpageAction.search.mms_results.xml.do%3FxmlFileName%3Dsearch.mms_results.xml&pageViewMode%3DEdit&pageBean.securityHashToken%3D-7577041729261673146 that  9938589053506421 is suppressed. @mzelesky can give us a better idea of what is going on with this record and with the content of issue #824
Based on the publishing profile details the 950 | a is as stated on #824 'Suppress from publishing'. But I'm not sure yet why this record has a different value.

The second `950` field has in `|a` value 'true' which means that it is suppressed. Maybe the record is corrupted and shouldn't have the first 950. https://github.com/pulibrary/marc_liberation/issues/993#issuecomment-767048517

So this is an example where there is a 950 field in the actual bib record that conflicts with the 950 created by the publishing enrichment.

I think the only real way to tackle this is to create a normalization process for catalogers that removes all fields from the bib record upon saving that the publishing job adds (950, 876, 852, 866, etc.), then run a periodic cleanup job on the records to remove those fields from records that missed the normalization.

So if there are traject errors related to unparseable fields (like the above fields), the best we can probably do is skip the record and report it out somehow. Otherwise you would have to add a lot of checking to remove fields that shouldn't be there.

One final note on this: it is possible to mark suppressed records as 'deleted' in the leader for the publishing job. This would be a more reliable way to exclude suppressed records than searching for a 950 field. This particular record is suppressed.

Okay skip it and report it is what we've done here in #1002 so I'm going to close this issue. The suppressed discussion should take place on #824. We'll talk about it at checkin today and then I will update that issue.

comments.body: How to tell whether a record is suppressed is unclear, as is what to do with a suppressed record. blocked pending specification.

We can turn on a flag in the publishing job to mark suppressed records as 'deleted' in the leader, which is less prone to cataloger error than the 950 field.

The sixth character of the leader would be a 'd'.
@mzelesky yes we can do that. I think it's a better option.
